The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                      IN THE CITY
                  
	 Chirag Uniteds Eduardo was Monday suspended for three months and fined Rs 2 lakh by the Indian Football Associations disciplinary committee.       
	During last years CFL Premier Division decider, Eduardo and teammate Denson Devadas had heckled referee Minangshu Bhattacharya for awarding a penalty to Mohun Bagan.       
	While Eduardo was punished, Denson was let off the hook for his stupendous performance in the Santosh Trophy.                
	 A blood donation camp was organised by the West Bengal Voluntary Blood Donors Association at the Netaji Indore Stadium on Monday. A total of 1240 donors came to give blood at the event supported by IFA.                
	 Shibaji Roy clinched a treble at the All Bengal BBS table tennis championship, organised by the Bhowanipur Bayam Sangha under the BTTA.       
	Shibaji emerged winner in the boys category, defeating Souvik Chowdhury 11-7, 11-9, 3-11, 9-11, 8-11, 11-9, 11-7.       
	He added the cadet boys title defeating Nilanjan Sarkar 11-9, 14-12, 5-11, 11-9. He annexed his third crown in the nursery boys category where he beat Soham Bhattacharjeee 12-10, 11-8.       
	Ria Dutta won two titles at the meet  the womens singles and the girls singles titles.       
	Other winners      
	Mens singles: Sumit Das; Sub-junior boys: Rohan Biswas; Sub-junior girls: Survi Patnari; Cadet girls: Ritiwa Kundu; Nursey girls: Nivedita Halder                
	 Howrah Hockey Training centre thrashed Khalsa Hockey Coaching Centre 5-0 to win the 12th edition of the Dhyan Chand Memorial hockey tournament (U-14) at the Sports Authority of India, Eastern Centre, Monday.      
	In the semi-final of the womens hockey tournament at the same venue, Young Star Hockey Training Centre drubbed Dasgram Samilita Sangha 9-0.       
	They will play Bow Hockey Association in the final after they beat Howrah Hockey Training Centre 2-0.                
	Hockey: Final of Womens Tournament, at SAI, from 3pm      
	Soccer: CFL match from 3:30pm                                                                                                                                                      
